      "body": "GR full build blocked: ~12 pre-existing v4.31 errors in SectionGradedRing + GrassmannianQuot\n\nThe roadmap tracked only **GR 3 sorrys** (all in `GlueDescent.lean`), but a full `lake build` of GR-Quot-Closure fails with **~12 hard compile errors** (not sorrys) in files the roadmap treated as done:\n\n- `SectionGradedRing.lean` \u2014 **8 errors** (lines 1546, 1664, 1704, 1888, 1935, 2640, 3173, 3840). Deep **v4.31 monoidal/braided-category API** breaks: braiding naturality (`\u03b2_`, `\u25b7`, `\u25c1`), `Localization.Monoidal.\u03bc` isos, `sheafificationCounitIso` `rfl`s, `synthInstance` failures. Its `TO_USER.md` still claims this file is \"sorry-free\".\n- `GrassmannianQuot.lean` \u2014 **4 errors** (lines 835, 912, 2396, 3350): `rw` \"did not find pattern\" + `simp made no progress`.\n\n**Cause:** these were almost certainly masked by **stale oleans** from before the v4.31 bump; the errors surface only on a clean rebuild. `SectionGradedRing.lean` does **not** import `GlueDescent`, so they are independent of this round's `GlueDescent` edits (proof-body-only, same signatures).\n\n**Impact:** GR-Quot-Closure cannot go green until these are migrated. This is a larger, separate task than \"restore the 3 GlueDescent sorrys\".\n\n**Next action:** schedule a dedicated v4.31 monoidal-API migration pass over `SectionGradedRing.lean` and `GrassmannianQuot.lean`.",
