      "body": "Two v4.31 sorrys remain hard: rawPushPullMap_comp (Cech) + pullback_cast_compat (GR)\n\nBoth survived this round and are **also sorry in the AJC copy** \u2014 genuinely hard, not quick.\n\n- `CechHigherDirectImage.lean` `rawPushPullMap_comp` (final step): needs `congrArg (pushforward p\u2081).map INNER` transported across an over-triangle `eqToHom (congrArg _ (Category.assoc b a p\u2081))`. Every route fails: `convert \u2026 using 2` leaves defeq instance/obj + HEq `map_comp` residuals even under the transparency option; `rw [he, \u2190 Functor.map_comp]`, `simp only [he, \u2190 Functor.map_comp]`, and `rw [\u2190 Category.assoc] at INNER` all hit **\"motive is not type correct\"** (the eqToHom depends on `Category.assoc b a p\u2081`). `INNER`/`he` (the math) ARE established. Try `conv`-mode or manual `Eq.mpr` assembly.\n- `GlueDescent.lean` `pullback_cast_compat` (line ~2033): a 7-term pullback-pseudofunctor cast-coherence identity with hypotheses `hpair`/`hmid`/`htriple` (no single `subst` variable). Original proof was \"in git\" but the git baseline has no history (baseline == interim). Needs a real coherence argument or the neighboring `comp5_rearrange`/`comp4_solve_front`/`map_fold\u2085` helpers.",
